Soundness CLI — Quick Start & Recovery Guide


Step 1 – Update your system

```sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade -y```


Step 2 – Install Soundnessup

```curl -sSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/soundnesslabs/soundness-layer/main/soundnessup/install | bash```


Step 3 – Install Rust

```curl --proto '=https' --tlsv1.2 -sSf https://sh.rustup.rs/ | sh```


Step 4 – Reload your shell

```source ~/.bashrc```


Step 5 – Install Soundness CLI

```soundnessup install```


Step 6 – Update Soundness CLI

```soundnessup update```


Step 7 – Generate a new key

```soundness-cli generate-key --name my-key```

⚠️ This will display your 24-word seed phrase  store it safely, offline.


Step 8 – Import an existing key

If you already have your 24-word seed phrase, you can recover your account without keystore.json:
```soundness-cli import-key --name my-key --mnemonic "word1 word2 word3 ... word24"```

Replace "word1 ... word24" with your actual seed phrase.
You can choose a different --name if you want to store multiple keys.
